I mean, I guess it's fine. It's your typical Dunkin' Donuts, but what sort of kills it for me so often here are the other customers. Had a woman come in and out of the blue start screaming, swearing, and berating a cashier with sexual epithets for no reason other than the cashier asked her if she could help her. Other times I've waited in line for an extended period of time while I waited for the cashier to stop having a conversation with a friend/customer.  Coffee is fine. Again, it's no better or worse from a food and beverage perspective than other locations....except....whenever I get a toasted bagel it doesn't really taste toasted? I think it's just run through really fast, like enough to melt the butter but not enough to make it crunchy/toasty.  Yes, they are open 24/7 which is a plus. Yes, they do have some outdoor seating, but I've never been able to be outside this location for more than a minute without being begged for change. The inside is small and all seats are almost always taken up by Harold Washington students from across the street.  There are tons of Dunkin' Donuts up and down Lake street. So if you have the time, maybe walk a block down to a different one.

Unfortunately there's no wifi - but they do have several USB and Electrical outlet ports, and are relatively clean (especially compared to their neighboring counter parts.)
